Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, to sharpish turn. Clay near fine buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster and caduceus symbols and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Midas
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1018)
